The formula ends up looking a lot like the hit rate
formula,\. but it can scale a bit higher.\. Additionally,\.
there is no longer the ability to "miss", in the sense
of how one would "miss" in a traditional battle.
As in,\. an attacker cannot miss from having a low
hit rate like you could before,\. regardless of the
target's stats.\. You can literally miss though, by
swinging randomly while no enemies are about.
You can still be evaded if the enemy's evasion is
high enough,\. but there is no longer a "miss" check.\.\.

In addition to randomly parrying,\. if you haven't accidentally
learned already,\. you can also \C[1]Guard\C[0] by holding
your \I[343] button,\. or if using the keyboard,\. the \C[2]SHIFT\C[0]
key (the same one you normally hold for dashing).
However,\. INSTEAD of dashing,\. your player will pivot
in-place.\.\. If an offhand is equipped that has a
guard-typed skill (see the database for examples),\. you
will hold up a shield and defend yourself!
There is no limit to how long you hold the defensive
position,\. however,\. if the guard skill has a \C[1]<parry:number>\C[0]
tag in the notes,\. it will grant it a brief window where
an incoming attack will be parried.
